# Migration Proposal — `{{source_basename}}` → `{{target_basename}}`

Generated by `/team-os-setup --migrate {{source_basename}}` (Step 9.6 → M2). Reads audit doc → produces manifest.

**AUDIT:** [migration-audit-{{date}}.md](migration-audit-{{date}}.md)

## Outcome

After execute:

```
{{vault_root}}/
├── {{target_basename}}/      [NEW or RENAMED — gitignored from parent if nested repo]
│   └── (consolidated content; full layout in manifest below)
├── 04 Archive/
│   └── {{source_basename}} (archived-{{date}})/      [SAFETY COPY — .git stripped]
└── (other vault content unchanged)

REMOVED:
  {{l1_basename}}/       (content merged into {{target_basename}}/)
  {{source_basename}}/   (content lives in {{target_basename}}/ + archive copy)
```

## Manifest — file-by-file

### Bucket 1: COPY — Source → Target

| Source path | Target path |
|---|---|
| `{{source}}/...` | `{{target}}/...` |
| ... | ... |

### Bucket 2: KEEP L1 — L1 versions win

| L1 path | Reason |
|---|---|
| `{{l1}}/...` | (why L1 wins for this file) |

### Bucket 3: SKIP — source files NOT migrated

| Source path | Reason | Stays in |
|---|---|---|
| `{{source}}/...` | (why not migrated) | archive |

Skipped files are subject to the M4.10 reconciliation pass (sub-agent reads archive vs active and reports whether anything should be elevated).

### Bucket 4: DEFERRED — Hard questions

| Item | Question | Default |
|---|---|---|
| HMQ-1 | (the question) | (the default action) |

## Execution Sequence (M4)

Each step halts on failure. Per the commit retry contract in SKILL.md, M4.7 / M4.8 / M4.5b commits retry up to 3 times on transient cloud-sync errors.

1. **M4.1 — Pre-migration tag.** `git -C "{{source}}" tag -a "pre-migrate-{{date}}" -m "snapshot before /team-os-setup --migrate"`.
2. **M4.2 — Archive.** `mkdir -p "04 Archive"`; add `04 Archive/` to parent `.gitignore` if not already; `cp -R "{{source}}" "04 Archive/{{source_basename}} (archived-{{date}})"`; strip `.git/` from archive copy if source was `own_repo`.
3. **M4.3 — Copy source content into L1** per Bucket 1.
4. **M4.4 — Move `.git`** from source to L1 (only if `own_repo`).
5. **M4.5 — Remove source folder** (content is safely in archive + L1).
6. **M4.5b — Parent-repo housekeeping** (only when L1 is nested inside a parent vault repo).
7. **M4.6 — Rename L1 → target.**
8. **M4.7 — Commit reorganization inside new repo.** Scope-staged.
9. **M4.8 — Commit parent vault repo.** Scope-staged.
10. **M4.9 — Verify** (9 checks per SKILL.md).
11. **M4.10 — Reconciliation gate** (sub-agent compares archive vs active for skipped-file elevation, duplicate audit, hardcoded-path audit).

## Risks + Mitigations

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Disk space for archive copy | Pre-check `df -h` before authorizing |
| `.git` move fails mid-op | Single `mv` is atomic on same filesystem; archive copy is the rollback |
| Pre-existing dirty files in parent rolled into commit | M0 check 5 → scoped-staging mode honored at M4.8 + M4.5b |
| Cloud-sync filesystem flake (Egnyte, Dropbox, OneDrive) | Commit retry contract (3 attempts with 2s backoff) per SKILL.md |
| Target folder name already exists | M0 pre-check; halt with rename suggestion |
| Hardcoded paths in `.claude/hooks/` reference old name | M4.10 hardcoded-path audit surfaces them (read-only report) |
| User wants different bucket decisions | M3 gate is the negotiation point; "defer to reconciliation" is an option |
